Decisions handed down May 9,1893.

Michael Murphy, Respondent, v. Hugh Graham as Executor of the Last Will and Testament of William Carroll, Deceased, Appellant. Mem. by Herrick, J.:

The questions involved in this case are entirety of fact, and while there is a conflict of evidence, there is evidence to sustain the findings of the referee, and I can find no sufficient reas m t) reverse such findings. The judgment should be affirmed, with costs. Mayham, P. J., concurred. Judgment affirmed, with costs.
